Job description:
Company Description
Literati is transforming education through deep personalization of books for every child. We believe the right books in the right hands at the right time can be life-changing, and we’re looking for a Backend Software Engineer to help us write the next chapter at Literati.
Founded in 2017, Literati is on a mission to inspire a love of learning through personally-curated book discovery. Our team of engineers, data scientists, creative thinkers, and unabashed book lovers have helped deliver over 5 million books to families across the US, with machine learning and proprietary reverse-logistics technology powering our Austin fulfillment center. Recently, we’ve expanded our reach into school book fairs, leveraging new systems and technology to deliver a modern, impeccably-designed book fair to students and educators.
Literati is the fastest-growing company in Arts & Literature in the US. We were recently ranked #3 on Inc’s Fastest Growing Companies in Austin, and named a 2022 Midsize Best Place to Work by Built In Austin. Our founder and CEO, Jessica Ewing, was named one of “Google’s Top 12 Most Innovative Minds” by Fast Company. We’ve raised over $60M in venture capital to date, with key investors including Founders Fund, General Catalyst, Felicis, and 01A (Dick Costolo and Adam Bain, former CEO and COO of Twitter).
ABOUT THE TEAM:
Our engineering team is responsible for building, architecting, deploying, maintaining, and enhancing our proprietary fulfillment and reverse-logistics systems that run our fulfillment centers, servicing both our subscription service and our book fairs. Our consumer engineering team is responsible for the customer facing interfaces including our site, app (web, native iOS and Android), subscription systems and marketing funnel. Our engineering team also works closely with our team of data scientists to deploy algorithms into production and run A/B tests across the company.

Literati's technical teams are mission-driven, thoughtful, curious and academic. If you’re looking for an army of tech bros, this probably isn’t the right fit for you. We value coaching, learning and development.

Job Description
As a Backend Software Engineer focused on getting the best books into the hands of every customer, you will play a crucial role in integrating our homegrown ML algorithms with our backend WMS system. You will focus on optimizing the integration with the algorithm team, developing ways to A/B test newer versions of the algorithm, and paving the way to integrate other ML algorithms into different areas of the business.
YOU'RE GOOD AT:

Building real-time, cloud-based web services and APIs that serve as the backbone for reliable/scalable applications;
Collaborating with Product Owners, Data Scientists, Engineers, and Customers on both ends of the spectrum;
Implementing and documenting engineering processes and standards;
Developing tests which ensure performance, quality, and scalability;
Working with product and customers to define requirements to build out new features.

YOUR DAY-TO-DAY WILL LOOK LIKE:

Working with product owners/managers across the company, you’ll participate in sprint grooming, planning, retrospective sessions.
Working with data/ML teams, you will define requirements, prioritize work, and come up with creative solutions that provide Literati with flexibility on its ML journey.
Working with Engineering, you’ll incorporate your expertise into our overall Engineering craft to achieve efficient delivery of our software products to market.

Qualifications*
YOU WILL NEED: *

3+ years experience defining and leading large-scale web application server architecture initiatives;
Experience building back end systems that integrate with ML algorithms and their outputs;
Industry leading skills in API and Data Model design;
Experience scaling infrastructure to support high-throughput/high-volume data pipelines;
Ability to efficiently communicate architectural perspectives and monitor implementations across internal teams;
Track record of successful delivery in an agile environment;
Demonstrated experience with common tools such as Git, Clubhouse/Jira, etc.;
Demonstrated leadership abilities in an engineering environment through driving operational excellence and best practices and mentoring junior developers
Experience with a Literati’s tech stack (Python/Django, Kubernetes, GCP, etc.) is a big plus.

Additional Information
We seek people with drive and a touch of alchemy—and if that sounds like you, you should join us. Even if your experience isn’t a precise match for the role, passion and prowess will always win the day in our book. And if your career has taken you to some spectacular (or spectacularly strange) places? We love a good story.
At Literati, we value the power of reading for all: anyone who dreams, anyone who wonders, anyone of any age, from any background. We are dedicated to cultivating and preserving a culture of inclusion and connectedness that sees, reflects, welcomes, and celebrates the innovation and talent of a diverse array of people.

Location: 1145 West 5th Street, Austin, TX 78703

Job Type: Full-time
